{"title":"Random Bolt","url":"http://crawl.chaosforge.org/Random_Bolt","type":"markdown","data":"***Obsolete**: This article refers to an aspect of the game which has been removed. It is retained for historical reference only.*\n\n|   |                                                                                                          |\n| - | -------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |\n|   | Fires, at random, a bolt of venom, negative energy, fire, cold, dispelling energy, electricity, or acid. |\n\n**Random Bolt** is a monster spell which randomly selects and fires one of the following bolts:\n\n- [Bolt of Fire](/Bolt_of_Fire \"Bolt of Fire\")\n- [Bolt of Cold](/Bolt_of_Cold \"Bolt of Cold\")\n- [Venom Bolt](/Venom_Bolt \"Venom Bolt\")\n- [Bolt of Draining](/Bolt_of_Draining \"Bolt of Draining\")\n- [Quicksilver Bolt](/Quicksilver_Bolt \"Quicksilver Bolt\")\n- [Corrosive Bolt](/Corrosive_Bolt \"Corrosive Bolt\")\n- [Lightning Bolt](/Lightning_Bolt \"Lightning Bolt\")\n\n## History\n\n- Random bolt was removed in [0.27](/0.27 \"0.27\"). The only enemy that had the spell was [Mnoleg](/Mnoleg \"Mnoleg\").\n- Prior to [0.19](/0.19 \"0.19\"), there was another monster with this spell, [Chaos champion](/Chaos_champion \"Chaos champion\").\n- Prior to [0.18](/0.18 \"0.18\"), the player had an access to this spell through the [rod of destruction](/Rod_of_destruction \"Rod of destruction\"). Also, [Mnoleg](/Mnoleg \"Mnoleg\") didn't have this spell.\n- Prior to [0.17](/0.17 \"0.17\"), [Crystal Bolt](/Crystal_Bolt \"Crystal Bolt\") was one of the possible bolts.\n- In [0.16](/0.16 \"0.16\"), [Corrosive Bolt](/Corrosive_Bolt \"Corrosive Bolt\") was added to the list of possible bolts.\n- Prior to [0.14](/0.14 \"0.14\"), Random Bolt was a level 5 spell.\n","html":"<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html class=\"client-nojs\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<head>\n<meta charset=\"UTF-8\"/>\n<title>Random Bolt - CrawlWiki</title>\n